        <link rel="schema.DC" href="https://purl.org/DC/elements/1.0/" /><meta name="citation_journal_title" content="RadioGraphics" /><meta name="dc.Title" content="Building a Bridge to Save a Failing Ventricle: Radiologic Evaluation of Short- and Long-term Cardiac Assist Devices" /><meta name="dc.Creator" content="Inas  Mohamed" /><meta name="dc.Creator" content="Charles T.  Lau" /><meta name="dc.Creator" content="Michael A.  Bolen" /><meta name="dc.Creator" content="Ahmed H.  El-Sherief" /><meta name="dc.Creator" content="Joseph T.  Azok" /><meta name="dc.Creator" content="Jamshid H.  Karimov" /><meta name="dc.Creator" content="Nader  Moazami" /><meta name="dc.Creator" content="Rahul D.  Renapurkar" /><meta name="dc.Description" content="Familiarity with cardiac support devices, their mechanisms of action, and normal and abnormal imaging appearances allows a radiologist to tailor CT protocols to address the relevant clinical questi..." /><meta name="Description" content="Familiarity with cardiac support devices, their mechanisms of action, and normal and abnormal imaging appearances allows a radiologist to tailor CT protocols to address the relevant clinical questi..." /><meta name="dc.Description" content="Heart failure is recognized with increasing frequency worldwide and often progresses to an advanced refractory state. Although the reference standard for treatment of advanced heart failure remains..." /><meta name="Description" content="Heart failure is recognized with increasing frequency worldwide and often progresses to an advanced refractory state. Although the reference standard for treatment of advanced heart failure remains..." /><meta name="dc.Publisher" content="Radiological Society of North America" /><meta name="dc.Date" scheme="WTN8601" content="2015-03-12" /><meta name="dc.Type" content="research-article" /><meta name="dc.Format" content="text/HTML" /><meta name="dc.Identifier" scheme="manuscript" content="140149" /><meta name="dc.Identifier" sch